From Lynn Anderson dba Subject Revised Easy to Read BoM available I am pleased to announce that a revised version of The Easy to Read Book of Mormon former title Mormon's Book by Lynn Matthews Anderson is now available through anonymous ftp see information below In addition to the change in title the revised ETR BOM has been shortened by several pages eliminating many extraneous that's and of's and many minor errors have been This release includes a simplified Joseph Smith Story testimonies of the three and eight witnesses and a Words to Know As with the previous announcement readers are reminded that this is a not for profit This is a copyrighted work but people are welcome to make verbatim copies for personal People can recuperate the actual costs of printing paper copy center charges but may not charge anything for their time in making copies or in any way realize a profit from the use of this See the permissions notice in the book itself for the precise Negotiations are currently underway with a Mormon publisher vis a vis the printing and distribution of bound Sorry I'm out of the wire bound first I will make another announcement about the availability of printed copies once everything has been worked FTP information connect via anonymous ftp to then cd pub you won't see anything at all until you do The Easy to Read Book of Mormon is currently available in postscript and RTF rich text format ASCII LaTeX and other versions can be made available contact for You should be able to print the postscript file on any postscript printer such as an Apple Laserwriter let dba know if you have any The postscript in the last release had problems on some printers this time it should work RTF is a standard document interchange format that can be read in by a number of word processors including Microsoft Word for both the Macintosh and If you don't have a postscript printer you may be able to use the RTF file to print out a copy of the r r r dba Apr r r r dba Apr For more information about how this project came about please refer to my article in the current issue of Sunstone entitled Delighting in Plainness Issues Surrounding a Simple Modern English Book of Send all inquiries and comments to Lynn Matthews Anderson Hampton Street Pittsburgh PA dba